                    <msContents>
                        <summary>This illustrated manuscript of the <title>Anvār-i Suhaylī</title>
                            (Lights of Canopus), a prose rescension of animal fables of Indian
                            origin known as <title>Kalīlah wa Dimnah</title>, composed by
                                <persName>Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ Kāshifī (ca. 1436–1504)</persName> opens and
                            closes with two double-page Safavid-era paintings and depictive colophon
                            featuring outdoor scenes. Divided into fourteen chapters, the author
                            composed for and dedicated it to the Timurid-era prince Niẓām al-Dīn
                            Shaykh Aḥmad Suhaylī (d. either 907 or 918 AH/1501 or 1512 CE). Famed
                            calligrapher <persName role="scr ato" key="person_96566676"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/96566676">Mīr ‘Alī Haravī</persName>
                            completed the text, probably in <placeName
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002243" key="place_7002243"
                                >Herat</placeName>, in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                notBefore="1504-07-01" notAfter="1504-07-15">mid-Muḥarram 910 AH
                                (early July 1504 CE)</date>, the year of the author's
                            death.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_18-item1">
                            <author key="person_90770167" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d.
                                    1504 or 5</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">كاشفى، حسين واعظ</persName>
                            </author>
                            <editor role="scr ato" key="person_96566676"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/96566676"><persName
                                    xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Mīr ‘Alī Haravī
                                    al-Ḥusaynī, ca. 1476–1544</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">میر علی هروی الحسینی</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <editor key="person_f4095" role="pat dte">
                                <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Suhaylī, Niẓām
                                    al-Dīn Aḥmad, d. 1501</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">نظام الدين احمد سهیلی</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20597" change="#ids-cleanup"
                                >Anvār-i Suhaylī</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20597" change="#ids-cleanup">انوار
                                سهيلی</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="3b" to="3b"> برگ ۳پ
                                    (folio 3b):</locus> حمد و ستایش خدای را غر اسمه که آثار قدرت او
                                بر چهره روز روشن تا بان است و انوار حکمت او در دل شب تار در فشان
                                بخشاینده که تار عنکبوت را پرده عصمت دوستان کرد </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                                <locus from="252a" to="252a"> برگ ۲۵۲ر (folio 252a):</locus> جو نگه
                                بدین پایه رسانم کلام * به که کنم خبم سخن و السلام. </explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="252a" to="252a"> برگ ۲۵۲ر (folio
                                    252a):</locus> وقد تمّ الکتاب بعون الملک الوهّاب علی ید الفقیر
                                علی کاتب تجاوز الله عن سیانه تحریراً فی اواسط شهر محرم الحرام سنه
                                عشر و تسعمایه الهجریه النبویه </colophon>
                            <colophon>Completed by <persName role="scr ato" key="person_96566676"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/96566676">‘Alī al-Kātib </persName>,
                                in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1504-07-01"
                                    notAfter="1504-07-15">mid-Muḥarram 910 AH (early July 1504
                                    CE)</date>.</colophon>

                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
